### 1.2 GTH Reference Clocks

AC coupling is on the SOM side (DEC-049; SOM schematic sheet 10). No carrier
coupling caps needed. Carrier trace runs J4 → J2 (connector-to-connector).

| Group | Signal | P net | N net | SOM/FPGA ball | Reference |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| GTH REFCLK | REFCLK0 | FMC_D04_GBTCLK0_M2C_P | FMC_D05_GBTCLK0_M2C_N | D10/D9 → JX2.D26/D27 | adrv9009_signals.sch; DEC-049 |
| GTH REFCLK | REFCLK1 | FMC_B20_GBTCLK1_M2C_P | FMC_B21_GBTCLK1_M2C_N | B10/B9 → JX2.C27/C28 | adrv9009_signals.sch; DEC-049 |

### 1.3 LVDS Sync / SYSREF Pairs (Bank 65, via J1/JX1)

These are LVCMOS18 LVDS signals routed from J4 (FMC) across the carrier to J1
(JX1 carrier socket → FPGA Bank 65). No AC coupling caps on carrier.

| Group | Signal | P net (carrier) | N net (carrier) | FPGA HP_DP alias | JX1 pins | Reference |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| LVDS | sysref | FMC_G06_LA00_CC_P | FMC_G07_LA00_CC_N | HP_DP_33_GC_P/N | C31/C32 | adrv9009_signals.sch; DEC-049 |
| LVDS | sysref_out | FMC_D08_LA01_CC_P | FMC_D09_LA01_CC_N | HP_DP_32_GC_P/N | D32/D33 | adrv9009_signals.sch; DEC-049 |
| LVDS | tx_sync | FMC_H07_LA02_P | FMC_H08_LA02_N | HP_DP_30_P/N | B28/B29 | adrv9009_signals.sch; DEC-049 |
| LVDS | rx_sync | FMC_G09_LA03_P | FMC_G10_LA03_N | HP_DP_46_P/N | B42/B43 | adrv9009_signals.sch; DEC-049 |
| LVDS | rx_os_sync | FMC_G27_LA25_P | FMC_G28_LA25_N | HP_DP_26_P/N | A28/A29 | adrv9009_signals.sch; DEC-049 |

### 1.4 Other Differential Pairs

No USB SuperSpeed (SS) lanes present in design. No other differential pairs
identified in the netlist beyond the groups above. Single-ended `_N` suffix
signals (SOM_RESET_IN_N, CC_RESET_OUT_N, etc.) are active-low LVCMOS, not diff
pairs.

