## 2. Impedance Targets

### 2.1 JESD204B GTH Lane Impedance

**Target: Zdiff = 100 Ω ± 10%, ZO = 50 Ω to ground.**

> "All JESD204B lane traces must be impedance controlled to achieve 50 Ω to
> ground. It is recommended that the differential pair be coplanar and loosely
> coupled."
> — ADRV9009 Data Sheet Rev B, §JESD204B Trace Routing Recommendations, p113

> "Route the differential pairs on a single plane using a solid ground plane as
> a reference on the layers above and below these traces."
> — ADRV9009 DS Rev B, §Routing Recommendations, p112

**Source confirmed on-disk:** ADRV9009.pdf → /tmp/adrv9009_ds.txt, lines
26449–26454 and 26540–26548.

Loose coupling geometry example from ADRV9009 DS (Figure 444, p113):
- Trace width: 5 mil (127 µm)
- Edge-to-edge spacing within pair: 15 mil (381 µm)
- "Loosely coupled" (not tightly coupled)

**[TO CONFIRM]** Trace width/spacing for our specific stackup (8-layer, dielectric
TBD with fab). Compute from impedance calculator once fab stackup is locked.

### 2.2 GTH Reference Clock Impedance

**Target: ZO = 50 Ω (= Zdiff = 100 Ω).**

> "The REF_CLK_IN± signal trace and the SYSREF signal trace are impedance
> controlled for characteristic impedance (ZO) = 50 Ω."
> — ADRV9009 DS Rev B, §Routing Recommendations, p112

**Source confirmed on-disk:** ADRV9009.pdf → /tmp/adrv9009_ds.txt, line 26482.

Note: ADRV9009 REF_CLK_IN± requires a 100 Ω termination resistor placed near
the ADC's REF_CLK_IN± pins on the ADRV9009-W/PCBZ board (ADRV9009 DS, p114).
On our board, the refclk signals terminate at the JX2 connector (SOM side), and
the SOM's FPGA GTH reference clock input has internal termination. No external
termination resistor is required on the carrier for the FPGA side.

**[VERIFIED 2026-06-23]** UG576 v1.7.1 §5 Board Design Guidelines confirms
MGTREFCLKP/N is internally terminated with 100 Ω differential (UG576 text
line 30543). On-die calibrated termination; no external resistor required on
carrier. AC coupling (0.01 µF) on SOM side confirmed (DEC-049). Refclk trace
impedance 100 Ω differential is consistent with on-chip termination.
Note: RCAL calibration resistor (100 Ω precision, between MGTAVTTRCAL and
MGTRREF) is on the SOM PCB (FPGA package pins — not carrier responsibility);
correctly absent from carrier schematics.

### 2.3 LVDS Sync / SYSREF Impedance

**Target: Zdiff = 100 Ω ± 10%.**

> "All LVDS pairs must be length-matched to within 5 mils within each pair.
> Use 100-ohm differential impedance (target ~3.5 mil trace, ~5 mil gap on
> standard 4-layer FR4)."
> — Capture Guide (ADRV9009_UZEV_Schematic_Capture_Guide-1.pdf), §PCB Layout,
> p8 (on-disk: /tmp/capture_guide.txt, lines 652–653)

Note: The capture guide geometry (3.5 mil / 5 mil gap) is for 4-layer FR4.
Our board is 8-layer; actual trace/gap will differ. Recompute from fab stackup.

**[TO CONFIRM]** VITA 57.1 FMC spec §6.x for LA pair impedance requirement.
Standard VITA 57.1 requires 100 Ω differential for FMC differential pairs;
this is consistent with the capture guide and the ADRV9009 DS.

