## 4. AC Coupling Cap Placement Constraint Summary

| Cap pair | Lane | Position | Constraint |
|---|---|---|---|
| C21, C22 | TX DP1 (tx_data[0]) | Near J4 (FMC) | Within 2 mm of J4 pin field |
| C23, C24 | TX DP2 (tx_data[1]) | Near J4 (FMC) | Within 2 mm of J4 pin field |
| C25, C26 | TX DP0 (tx_data[2]) | Near J4 (FMC) | Within 2 mm of J4 pin field |
| C27, C28 | TX DP3 (tx_data[3]) | Near J4 (FMC) | Within 2 mm of J4 pin field |

Caps must be on the same side and layer as the FMC trace segment. P-cap and
N-cap for each lane must be placed symmetrically (equal distance from J4 pad,
equal stub length to cap pad).

