## 7. Candidate Stackup & Provisional Trace Geometry

> **PROVISIONAL — ALL VALUES IN THIS SECTION MUST BE CONFIRMED AGAINST THE
> FAB'S ACTUAL STACKUP BEFORE GERBER SIGN-OFF. Do not treat these as
> manufactured-board specifications.**

### 7.1 Candidate 8-Layer 1.6 mm FR4 Stackup

**Assumptions:**
- Total finished thickness: 1.6 mm (63.0 mil)
- Outer copper: 1 oz/ft² (34.8 µm = 1.4 mil)
- Inner copper: 0.5 oz/ft² (17.4 µm = 0.7 mil)
- Dk: 4.3 at mid-band FR4 (see note below)
- Symmetric construction (mirror symmetry at centre core)

Total copper: 2×1.4 + 6×0.7 = 7.0 mil; total dielectric: 56.0 mil; sum = 63.0 mil ✓

| Position | Layer / Interface | Material | Thickness (mil) | Thickness (µm) | Dk |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| L1 | **F.Cu** (outer, signal/escape) | 1 oz copper | 1.4 | 35 | — |
| L1→L2 | Prepreg | FR4 (e.g. 2×1080 or 1×2116) | **4.0** | 102 | 4.3 |
| L2 | **In1.Cu** (GND reference plane) | 0.5 oz copper | 0.7 | 18 | — |
| L2→L3 | Core | FR4 | **7.0** | 178 | 4.3 |
| L3 | **In2.Cu** (JESD204B + refclk) | 0.5 oz copper | 0.7 | 18 | — |
| L3→L4 | Core | FR4 | **7.0** | 178 | 4.3 |
| L4 | **In3.Cu** (GND reference plane) | 0.5 oz copper | 0.7 | 18 | — |
| L4→L5 | Core | FR4 (centre/thick core) | **20.0** | 508 | 4.3 |
| L5 | **In4.Cu** (power distribution) | 0.5 oz copper | 0.7 | 18 | — |
| L5→L6 | Core | FR4 | **7.0** | 178 | 4.3 |
| L6 | **In5.Cu** (LVDS sync/sysref) | 0.5 oz copper | 0.7 | 18 | — |
| L6→L7 | Core | FR4 | **7.0** | 178 | 4.3 |
| L7 | **In6.Cu** (GND reference plane) | 0.5 oz copper | 0.7 | 18 | — |
| L7→L8 | Prepreg | FR4 (e.g. 2×1080 or 1×2116) | **4.0** | 102 | 4.3 |
| L8 | **B.Cu** (outer, signal/escape) | 1 oz copper | 1.4 | 35 | — |
| | **TOTAL** | | **63.0 mil** | **1601 µm ≈ 1.6 mm** | |

**Material spec — MacroFab primary source (help.macrofab.com/knowledge/pcb-layer-stackups):**

| Property | Value | Condition | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| Material grade | TG-170 (FR4) | Platform default | Confirm exact grade at quote — platform dropdown shows "FR4-TG175"; minor naming discrepancy, flag at quote stage |
| Dk | 4.3–4.5 | @ 1 MHz | Primary-sourced |
| Dk | **3.8–4.0** | **@ 1 GHz** | **Primary-sourced — use for GHz-rate signals** |
| Loss tangent (tan δ) | 0.012–0.014 | @ 1 GHz | Primary-sourced |
| Min board thickness (8-layer) | 1.0 mm | Standard | Our 1.6 mm is within range ✓ |
| Board thickness tolerance | ±0.15 mm | At 1.6 mm nominal | Primary-sourced |

**Dk is frequency-dependent — use the correct value for each signal group:**
- **JESD204B SERDES + GTH refclks (GHz range):** use Dk = **3.9** (midpoint of 3.8–4.0
  @ 1 GHz). This is now **FAB-PRIMARY-SOURCED**. The prior §7 Rev 0.2 value of 4.3 was
  the 1 MHz figure — incorrect for GHz-rate signal impedance calculations. See §7.2.1
  for corrected trace geometry.
- **LVDS sync/sysref (sub-GHz — sysref ~7 MHz, sync ~100 MHz):** actual Dk at these
  frequencies is 4.1–4.4, between the 1 MHz and 1 GHz tabulated values. Dk = 3.9 is
  used in §7.2.2 for consistency and produces a slightly conservative (slightly wide)
  trace estimate. Actual impedance at sub-GHz will be within ±5% of the GHz calculation.

**Loss tangent / insertion loss awareness (JESD204B lanes):**
At 12 GHz, dielectric loss scales roughly linearly from the 1 GHz tan δ value.
Rough estimate for a 150 mm (6-inch) In2.Cu stripline at 12 GHz: dielectric loss
≈ 4–5 dB, conductor loss ≈ 2–3 dB, total ≈ 6–8 dB insertion loss. This approaches
the JESD204B receiver sensitivity limit and is consistent with the ADRV9009 DS note
that standard FR4 is acceptable for paths ≤ 6 inches but premium material
(RO4350B / RO4003C) is recommended beyond that. Our board (152.4 mm = 6.0 inches
maximum diagonal) is at the boundary. Confirm in SI simulation before finalising
routing if any lane approaches the maximum path length.

**Centre core note:** The 20.0 mil centre core provides warp symmetry for the finished
board. Its exact thickness is adjusted by the fab to meet total-thickness spec and may
differ from 20.0 mil; the signal layers (In2/In5) are unaffected because they reference
their immediate neighbour planes, not the centre core.

### 7.2 Controlled-Impedance Trace Geometry Estimates

**Formula used: Wheeler symmetric stripline (IPC-2141A Section 4.1)**

    Z₀ = (60 / √Dk) × ln[ 4b / (0.67π(0.8w + t)) ]

    where:
      w  = trace width (mil)
      t  = copper thickness (mil) = 0.7 mil (inner 0.5 oz)
      b  = total ground-plane separation (mil) = h_above + t + h_below
      Dk = dielectric constant:
             3.9 for GHz-rate signals (JESD/refclk) — MacroFab KB @ 1 GHz midpoint
             ~4.2 for sub-GHz LVDS — 3.9 used below for consistency (slightly conservative)

    Valid for w/b < 0.85. Check this after substituting fab stackup.

**Differential impedance (loosely coupled edge-coupled pair):**

    Zdiff ≈ 2 × Z₀  (valid when edge-to-edge spacing s ≥ 3×w)

    At s = 15 mil, w = 5 mil: s/w = 3.0 — borderline loose; coupling correction
    is < 3%, negligible relative to the ±10% impedance tolerance.

---

#### 7.2.1 In2.Cu — JESD204B Lanes and GTH RefClks (symmetric stripline)

Reference planes: In1.Cu (GND) above at 7.0 mil; In3.Cu (GND) below at 7.0 mil.

    h_above = 7.0 mil (CORE₂₃)
    h_below = 7.0 mil (CORE₃₄)
    b = 7.0 + 0.7 + 7.0 = 14.7 mil

**Corrected calculation at Dk = 3.9 (MacroFab @ 1 GHz, primary source):**

At w = 5 mil:

    Z₀ = (60/√3.9) × ln[4×14.7 / (0.67×π×(0.8×5 + 0.7))]
       = 30.38 × ln[58.8 / 9.893]
       = 30.38 × ln[5.944]
       = 30.38 × 1.783
       ≈ 54.2 Ω  (ESTIMATE)

    Zdiff ≈ 2 × 54.2 = 108 Ω  (ESTIMATE, s = 15 mil ETE) — slightly above 100 Ω target

Solve for w at Z₀ = 50 Ω exactly (Dk = 3.9): **w ≈ 5.9 mil**

Over full GHz Dk range (3.8–4.0): w = **5.7–6.0 mil**.
Provisional layout value: **w = 6 mil (152 µm)** — conservative end of the range.

**Correction direction (Dk 4.3 → 3.9):** Lower Dk raises Z₀ for fixed geometry
(Z₀ ∝ 1/√Dk). The prior Dk=4.3 estimate of w=5 mil already placed Zdiff above
100 Ω (≈103 Ω); at the correct Dk=3.9, the same 5 mil trace gives Zdiff≈108 Ω
(8% high). Correction is a **wider** trace — not narrower. Delta: +0.6–0.7 mil.

**Prior Dk = 4.3 calculation (1 MHz value — SUPERSEDED, shown for reference):**

    Z₀ = (60/√4.3) × ln[58.8/9.893] = 28.93 × 1.783 ≈ 51.6 Ω → Zdiff ≈ 103 Ω at w=5 mil
    w for Z₀=50 Ω: ≈ 5.3 mil

    Why wrong: Dk = 4.3 is the MacroFab material value @ 1 MHz, not the GHz-range
    value (3.8–4.0). Using the 1 MHz Dk for a 12 Gbps signal understates Z₀ by ~5%
    and produces a trace that is ~0.6 mil too narrow to hit 100 Ω.

| Parameter | Value | Unit | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| Signal layer | In2.Cu | — | locked (DEC-053) |
| Reference planes | In1.Cu (GND) + In3.Cu (GND) | — | locked |
| h_above / h_below | 7.0 / 7.0 | mil | ESTIMATE — fab to confirm |
| b (GND-to-GND) | 14.7 | mil | ESTIMATE |
| Dk | **3.9** (GHz midpoint) | — | FAB-PRIMARY-SOURCED — MacroFab KB 3.8–4.0 @ 1 GHz; prior value 4.3 was 1 MHz figure, SUPERSEDED |
| Trace width w | **6 mil (152 µm)** provisional | mil / µm | ESTIMATE — Dk=3.9; range 5.7–6.0 mil over Dk 3.8–4.0; prior Rev 0.2 value was 5 mil (wrong Dk=4.3, superseded) |
| Edge-to-edge spacing s | **15 mil (381 µm)** | mil / µm | from ADRV9009 DS Fig. 444; unchanged |
| Center-to-center pitch | 21 mil (533 µm) | mil / µm | ESTIMATE (6 + 15 = 21 mil) |
| Z₀ (single-ended) at w=6 mil | ≈ 49.4 Ω | Ω | ESTIMATE, Dk=3.9 |
| Zdiff (loose coupling) at w=6 mil | ≈ 98.8 Ω | Ω | ESTIMATE; target 100 Ω ±10% ✓ (within 2%) |
| Zdiff at w=5 mil (prior, superseded) | ≈ 108 Ω | Ω | ESTIMATE, Dk=3.9; within ±10% but 8% high; use w=6 mil |
| w/b validity check | 6/14.7 = 0.41 < 0.85 | — | formula valid ✓ |

**ADI-consistent; height assumption unstated.** The ADRV9009 DS (Figure 444, p113)
specifies 5 mil / 15 mil ETE for 100 Ω differential stripline with GND planes above
and below the signal layer (DS lines 26449–26454). The DS does **not** state the
dielectric height h (distance to reference plane) for this recommendation. The DS eval
board (ADRV9009-W/PCBZ) is a 14-layer board (JESD on Layer 5 and Layer 10), uses
FR4-370HR at Dk = 4.1 (stated in DS via-fence section, ~line 26670), and provides no
ground-plane separation value. Our candidate now uses Dk = 3.9 (MacroFab GHz primary source) and h = 7.0 mil. The
Dk is now primary-sourced; h remains an estimate pending the MacroFab custom-quote
stackup sheet. At w=6 mil the calculation yields Zdiff ≈ 105 Ω, within 100 Ω ±10%,
but this is a stackup-specific estimate, not DS-validated geometry for our particular h.

---

#### 7.2.2 In5.Cu — LVDS Sync / SYSREF (symmetric stripline, asymmetric references)

Reference planes: In4.Cu (power) above at 7.0 mil; In6.Cu (GND) below at 7.0 mil.
Geometry is identical to In2.Cu (b = 14.7 mil), so the impedance formula gives the
same result.

    b = 7.0 + 0.7 + 7.0 = 14.7 mil
    Dk = 3.9 (MacroFab @ 1 GHz; conservative for sub-GHz LVDS, actual Dk ~4.1–4.4)
    Z₀ ≈ 54.2 Ω at w = 5 mil  (ESTIMATE, Dk=3.9)
    Z₀ ≈ 49.4 Ω at w = 6 mil  (ESTIMATE, Dk=3.9)  ← provisional layout value
    Zdiff ≈ 105 Ω at w=6 mil, s = 15 mil ETE  (ESTIMATE)

| Parameter | Value | Unit | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| Signal layer | In5.Cu | — | locked (DEC-053) |
| Reference planes | In4.Cu (power) + In6.Cu (GND) | — | locked |
| Dk used | 3.9 (MacroFab @ 1 GHz; conservative for sub-GHz LVDS) | — | FAB-PRIMARY-SOURCED |
| Trace width w | **6 mil (152 µm)** provisional | mil / µm | ESTIMATE, Dk=3.9; same geometry as In2.Cu for simplicity |
| Edge-to-edge spacing s | **15 mil (381 µm)** | mil / µm | ESTIMATE |
| Z₀ (single-ended) at w=6 mil | ≈ 49.4 Ω | Ω | ESTIMATE, Dk=3.9 |
| Zdiff (loose coupling) at w=6 mil | ≈ 98.8 Ω | Ω | ESTIMATE; target 100 Ω ±10% ✓ (within 2%) |

**Power-plane reference note:** In4.Cu is a power distribution layer, not ground.
For differential (odd-mode) signals, the reference plane carries primarily common-mode
current; odd-mode current is contained between the trace pair. The impedance impact of
referencing a power plane vs. a GND plane is typically < 5% for Zdiff, well inside the
±10% tolerance. For LVDS at 1–200 MHz, this effect is further diminished by the low
frequency. If the fab's field solver shows deviation > 5%, route LVDS on In2.Cu instead.

---

#### 7.2.3 F.Cu / B.Cu — Outer Layer Microstrip (reference only)

These layers carry only short escape traces and LVCMOS single-ended signals (§5). No
controlled-impedance differential routing planned on outer layers. Provided for
reference if any future signal requires an outer-layer single-ended 50 Ω trace.

Formula: Wheeler microstrip (IPC-2141A):

    Z₀ = (87/√(Dk + 1.41)) × ln[5.98h / (0.8w + t)]

    h = 4.0 mil (PP₁₂ for F.Cu; PP₇₈ for B.Cu)
    t = 1.4 mil (1 oz outer copper)
    Dk = 4.3

    Solving for Z₀ = 50 Ω: w ≈ 5.8 mil → **use 6 mil (152 µm)**  (ESTIMATE)

---

### 7.3 Confidence Assessment

| Value | Classification | What it would take to firm it up |
|---|---|---|
| Dk = 3.9 (GHz) / 4.3–4.5 (1 MHz) | **FAB-PRIMARY-SOURCED** — MacroFab KB (help.macrofab.com/knowledge/pcb-layer-stackups) gives 3.8–4.0 @ 1 GHz, 4.3–4.5 @ 1 MHz. GHz value used for JESD/refclk. DS eval board uses Dk=4.1 (FR4-370HR, DS line ~26670) — consistent. | ✓ Sourced. Still confirm exact laminate grade (TG-170 vs TG-175) at quote |
| h_above = h_below = 7.0 mil | Textbook typical for 8L 1.6mm | Fab's stackup sheet (actual core/prepreg catalogue values; ±10% variation typical) |
| Wheeler Z₀ formula accuracy | Calculator-derived; ±5% vs. field-solver | Adequate for layout planning given ±10% impedance tolerance; re-run in field-solver (Polar SI, CITS880s) for controlled-impedance note |
| Zdiff ≈ 2×Z₀ approximation | Calculator-derived; < 3% error at s=15 mil | Adequate for loose coupling; confirmed by ADRV9009 DS using same geometry |
| w = 5 mil / s = 15 mil ETE | Derived from formula + DS-specified geometry | Consistent; adjust w in ≤ 0.5 mil steps once fab confirms Dk and h |
| Centre core = 20.0 mil | Chosen for thickness balance; structural | Fab will assign actual core catalogue value; does not affect signal layers |
| Via stub < 50 mil | Rule-of-thumb from Capture Guide | Field-solver or TDR measurement for final verification; adequate for planning |
| Outer microstrip w ≈ 6 mil | Calculator-derived reference | Not on critical path; compute at layout time if needed |

**Bottom line for layout start:** Route JESD/refclk on In2.Cu and LVDS on In5.Cu at
**w = 6 mil / s = 15 mil ETE** (Zdiff ≈ 99 Ω on candidate stackup, Dk=3.9 — right at 100 Ω target). Dk is
now fab-primary-sourced (MacroFab KB). Dielectric height h = 7.0 mil remains an
estimate — replace with MacroFab's custom controlled-impedance stackup heights before
setting the KiCad `.kicad_dru` DRC impedance rules file. At that point recompute w;
expect 5.7–6.0 mil across the Dk 3.8–4.0 range.

